  "texts": [
    "In contrast, a journal is called cross-field if it has multiple narrow field classifications in Scopus.",
    "Since Journal of Information Science is in two narrow fields (3309 Library and Information Sciences; 1709 Information Systems), it is cross-field here.",
    "This is an oversimplification for many reasons.",
    "First, a \"cross-field\" journal could be cross-field in the sense of deliberately including selected largely unrelated fields, cross-field in the sense of a generalist journal spanning multiple related fields, or inclusive/general in the sense of spanning many fields or all science (e.g., Science, Nature).",
    "Moreover, a journal might span a narrow field but have multiple classifications because the field crosses the border of two Scopus narrow fields, perhaps because it evolved after the Scopus classification scheme developed."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}